<number box="[938,951,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" value="6.0">6</number>
.– 
<date box="[970,1075,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" value="2010-03-07">7.3.2010</date>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known so far only from the Arava valley (
<collectingCountry box="[836,901,188,213]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Israel</collectingCountry>
) and from Palmyra (
<collectingCountry box="[1133,1198,188,213]" name="Syria" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Syria</collectingCountry>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Pollen hosts.</emphasis>
Possibly oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName box="[643,735,225,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
